The paper analyzes the computational complexity of market maker pricing algorithms for combinatorial prediction markets, which involves game theory (cs.GT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also proposes an approximation technique based on online learning, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
